Comparing different statistics (Figure 8)

Testing the difference of different statistics (Wilcoxon test), the data was transformed for plotting.

Effect size is given by \(\frac{|\bar{x} - \bar{y}|}{SD}\). All tests conducted are Wilcoxon sum rank test, which do not require assumptions regarding the underlying distribution of observations.

Testing Length

Comparing lengths of TD and NTDs session. Not relevant since all endpoints are normalized per time.
